For example if I by a share at BSE, it's SEBI's responsibility to ensure that the share gets credited to my DMAT account. Unfortunately no government will want to solve this issue.

text: Thanks Akshat for this very informative video. The fear or doubts about crypto space is that, it's difficult to believe the "deregulated" networks because lack of accountability in case of something goes wrong. There are people behind the scene who are building the network. There are resources; infrastructure and human, who are not answerable to the small investors. There is no robust mechanism to support mishandling or any mishaps. In case of fiat money, there are different bodies, rules & regulations and huge  offline network supporting the mechanism. That is still evolving in terms of cryptos. Another point, isn't it better to use actual money instead of crypto for transactions for any economy? How will govt function if they aren't stakeholder?
